# Code Quality and Formatting

## ESLint
ESLint configuration is defined in [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs). Follow these guidelines:

- Fix all ESLint warnings and errors before committing
- No console.log statements in production code
- Use optional chaining (?.) for nullable objects
- Use nullish coalescing (??) for null/undefined fallbacks
- Maintain consistent import ordering
- Use named exports over default exports
- Keep files under 400 lines of code
- Maximum line length is 100 characters

## Code Organization
- One component per file
- Group related components in feature directories
- Keep components pure when possible
- Extract complex logic into custom hooks
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions